result.execSummary:
The defendant was charged with both OWI (4th) and Operating w/ PAC (4th). The defendant was found guilty of OWI (4th) and the other charge, Operating w/ PAC (4th) was dismissed by the court.

  • Jerry L Maxwell was found guilty of OWI (4th), an unclassified misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 346.63(1)(a).

Charge(s) in this case were read in to this or other case(s). A "read in" charge is a charge that is dismissed as part of a plea agreement, however:

  • The defendant agrees to have the court consider the charge(s) when sentencing for another crime, under Wis. Stats. 973.20(1g)(b); and
  • The defendant cannot be prosecuted for these charge(s) in the future.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

Defendant Jerry L Maxwell in court, in custody, with attorney Joan B Broughton.    District Attorney's Office Law Intern, Lucas Bennewitz, appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Defendant enters a guilty plea to Count 1.  Court finds defendant guilty.  Count 2 dismissed and read in.  Count 3 dismissed by operation of law.

Court orders the following: 
- 1 year Huber with standard release conditions. STAYED.  Credit for 72 days if revoked.
- 1 year Probation
- 36 months Drivers License Revocation. 
- 36 months Ignition Interlock on any vehicle TITLED OR REGISTERED to defendant 
- Alcohol Assessment
- Attendance at the Victim Impact Panel meeting on either June 25, 2014 or the following one, or 30 days jail consecutive.
- Fine of $1,494.00 to be paid as a Condition of Probation
- Blood Test Reimbursement of $35.00 paid through Waukesha County Circuit Court to be forwarded to Waukesha Police Department
- Transcript fees of $10.00 to be paid as a Condition of Probation
- Defendant may complete 150 hours of Community Service in lieu of paying the fine, blood test reimbursement and transcript fee.
- DNA Surcharge waived.
- Conditions of Probation: Submit to an AODA assessment and follow through with any treatment/counseling.  Maintain absolute sobriety/Random UAs.  No use or possession of alcohol/drug paraphernalia/drugs without a valid prescription.  Valid prescriptions to be taken in the manner they were prescribed.  Maintain full-time employment and/or school.  

CONDITION TIME: 90 days - First 10 days - NON WORKING HOURS WITH STANDARD RELEASE CONDITIONS - To commence forthwith.  Last 80 days STAYED and defendant to be released to Day Report Center for compliance for 120 days.
